<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Guru_Rinpoche_-_Padmasambhava_statue.jpg" class="image" title="Founder of the Nyingma school of Tibetan Buddhism,  Padmasambhava, also known as Guru Rinpoche. Note the wide-open eyes, characteristic of a particular method of meditation.[1]"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Guru_Rinpoche_-_Padmasambhava_statue.jpg/180px-Guru_Rinpoche_-_Padmasambhava_statue.jpg" width="180" height="240" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Guru_Rinpoche_-_Padmasambhava_statue.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Founder of the Nyingma school of Tibetan Buddhism, <a href="/wiki/Padmasambhava" title="Padmasambhava">Padmasambhava</a>, also known as Guru Rinpoche. Note the wide-open eyes, characteristic of a particular method of meditation.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></div>
