<li id="cite_note-44"><b><a href="#cite_ref-44" title="">^</a></b> <i>Sang Shi</i> later became an abbot of <a href="/wiki/Samye" title="Samye">Samye</a> Monastery.</li>
<li id="cite_note-45"><b><a href="#cite_ref-45" title="">^</a></b> Barber, A. W.(1990). <i>The Unifying of Rdzogs Pa Chen Po and Ch'an</i>. Chung-Hwa Buddhist Journal. Vol.3, 04.1990. PP.301-317. Source: <a href="http://ccbs.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-BJ001/barber.htm" class="external autonumber" title="http://ccbs.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-BJ001/barber.htm" rel="nofollow">[1]</a> (accessed: October 20, 2007).</li>
